### 2. `draw_ui()` - Legal Destination Highlighting Redundancy

```c
// CURRENT PROBLEM: Called 64 times per frame, each calling gui_is_legal_move
// which internally calls gui_make_move + gui_find_king + gui_is_square_attacked
for (int c = 0; c < 8; c++) {
    // ...
    if (selected_sq != -1) {
        GuiMove test_m = {selected_sq, sq, 0};
        if (gui_is_legal_move(&current_state, test_m)) {  // 64x expensive call!
            is_legal_dest = 1;
        }
    }
}
```

**Optimized - precompute legal destinations once per frame:**
```c
// Add this before the render loop in draw_ui()
uint64_t legal_dest_mask = 0ULL; // Bitmask of legal destination squares

if (selected_sq != -1) {
    // Compute all legal destinations for selected piece ONCE
    // using the same targeted generation as optimized has_legal_moves
    int f = selected_sq;
    int p = current_state.board[f];
    int abs_p = abs(p);
    int fr = f / 8, fc = f % 8;
    
    // Reuse targeted move generation per piece type (same as above optimization)
    // Store results in bitmask
    for (int t = 0; t < 64; t++) {
        GuiMove test_m = {f, t, 0};
        if (abs_p == 1 && (t / 8 == 0 || t / 8 == 7)) test_m.promo = 5;
        if (gui_is_legal_move(&current_state, test_m)) {
            legal_dest_mask |= (1ULL << t);
        }
    }
}

// Then inside render loop replace the call with:
int is_legal_dest = (selected_sq != -1) && ((legal_dest_mask >> sq) & 1);
```
**Expected gain: Reduces from 64 legality checks to 1 bitmask lookup per square**

