## Summary Table

| Optimization | Estimated Speedup | Complexity |
|---|---|---|
| Targeted move generation in `has_legal_moves` | **20-40x** fewer calls | Medium |
| Cache legal dest bitmask in `draw_ui` | **64x** fewer checks/frame | Low |
| Cache king square in struct | **~10x** faster per legality check | Low |
| Cache repetition count | Eliminates redundant scans | Low |
| Incremental position string | Removes O(n) rebuild | Low |
| SAN disambiguation gate | Skips expensive checks usually | Low |
| Single-pass info line scanner | Minor, hot path cleanup | Low |

The **king square caching** and **targeted move generation** together will likely provide the most noticeable improvement on the 3DS ARM11 processor, since `gui_has_legal_moves` is called on nearly every frame and each call currently does up to 4096 full legality checks each doing a linear king search.
